   "source": [
    "# Trinity Attentional Gateway Probe — Selective Filtering\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task 11 of 25** | Track 3: Attention | Brain Zone: THALAMUS\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook measures a model's ability to filter relevant information from noise.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Trinity Neuroanatomical Foundation\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Thalamus** in Trinity implements attentional gating:\n",
    "\n",
    "```zig\n",
    "// src/tri/brain/thalamus_logs.zig\n",
    "pub const FilterConfig = struct {\n",
    "    focus: []const u8,  // Priority focus\n",
    "    suppress: []const u8,  // Noise suppression\n",
    "    threshold: f32,  # Attention threshold\n",
    "};\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Ternary Scoring {-1, 0, +1}\n",
    "\n",
    "- **+1 (correct)**: Model extracts signal correctly\n",
    "- **0 (partial)**: Model shows uncertainty about signal\n",
    "- **-1 (wrong)**: Model confused by noise\n",
    "\n",
    "### φ-Scaling\n",
    "\n",
    "Distractor count follows Fibonacci: 3, 5, 8, 13, 21"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install Kaggle Benchmarks SDK\n",
    "!pip install -q kaggle-benchmarks"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import kaggle_benchmarks as kbench\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from dataclasses import dataclass\n",
    "from typing import Literal\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load generated dataset\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../../data/tagp_attention.csv')\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(df)} items\")\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Filter for selective filtering task\n",
    "filter_df = df[df['task'] == 'Selective Filtering'].copy()\n",
    "print(f\"Selective filtering items: {len(filter_df)}\")\n",
    "filter_df[['id', 'task', 'context', 'query', 'distractor_count', 'difficulty']].head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define structured output for selective filtering\n",
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class FilteringResponse:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Model's response to filtering task.\"\"\"\n",
    "    extracted_signal: str  # The signal extracted from noise\n",
    "    confidence: float  # 0.0 to 1.0\n",
    "    noise_level: float  # Estimated noise level (0-1)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def ternary_score(self, expected_focus: str) -> Literal[-1, 0, 1]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Return Trinity ternary score {-1, 0, +1}.\"\"\"\n",
    "        # Correct: exact match\n",
    "        if self.extracted_signal == expected_focus:\n",
    "            return 1\n",
    "        # Partial: contains signal with uncertainty\n",
    "        elif 0.3 < self.confidence < 0.8 and self.noise_level > 0.3:\n",
    "            return 0\n",
    "        # Wrong: missed signal or overconfident\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            return -1\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"FilteringResponse schema defined\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define Kaggle benchmark task\n",
    "@kbench.task(name=\"trinity_thalamus_selective_filtering\")\n",
    "def selective_filtering(\n",
    "    llm: kbench.LLM,\n",
    "    context: str,\n",
    "    query: str,\n",
    "    expected_focus: str,\n",
    "    distractor_count: int\n",
    ") -> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Measure model's selective attention ability.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Filtering score: 1.0 (perfect) to -1.0 (worst)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    prompt = f\"\"\"Extract the relevant signal from this noisy context.\n",
    "\n",
    "Context (contains {distractor_count} distractors): {context}\n",
    "Query: {query}\n",
    "\n",
    "Provide:\n",
    "1. The extracted signal\n",
    "2. Your confidence (0.0 to 1.0)\n",
    "3. Your estimate of noise level (0.0 = clean, 1.0 = very noisy)\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    response = llm.prompt(\n",
    "        prompt,\n",
    "        schema=FilteringResponse\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate ternary score\n",
    "    ternary = response.ternary_score(expected_focus)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Combine: 50% accuracy, 30% confidence, 20% noise awareness\n",
    "    accuracy = 1.0 if response.extracted_signal == expected_focus else -1.0\n",
    "    confidence_score = (response.confidence - 0.5) * 2  # [-1, 1]\n",
    "    noise_bonus = (1.0 - abs(response.noise_level - 0.5)) * 0.2\n",
    "    \n",
    "    final_score = 0.5 * accuracy + 0.3 * confidence_score + noise_bonus\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return max(-1.0, min(1.0, final_score))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Task 'trinity_thalamus_selective_filtering' registered\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run evaluation on a sample\n",
    "sample_df = filter_df.head(10)  # Test with 10 items first\n",
    "\n",
    "results = selective_filtering.evaluate(\n",
    "    llm=[kbench.llm],  # Default test LLM\n",
    "    evaluation_data=sample_df\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Evaluation Results (Sample):\")\n",
    "print(f\"Mean Score: {results['score'].mean():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Std Dev: {results['score'].std():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Min: {results['score'].min():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Max: {results['score'].max():.4f}\")\n",
    "results.head()"
   ]
  },
